config BR2_PACKAGE_MIDILINK
	bool "midilink"
	depends on BR2_TOOLCHAIN_HAS_THREADS
	select BR2_PACKAGE_ALSA_LIB
	select BR2_PACKAGE_ALSA_LIB_SEQ
	help
	  MidiLink: the MiSTer-devel daemon that bridges ALSA-sequencer USB
	  MIDI adapters (Minimig, ao486, and other cores) to a real MIDI
	  port, a software synth (MUNT/mt32d -- package/munt -- or
	  FluidSynth), or a network peer (UDP/TCP, incl. a small Hayes "AT"
	  command subset). Stock ships it as /usr/sbin/midilink plus a
	  small companion tool /usr/sbin/mlinkutil (P0.3 inventory:
	  docs/stock-inventory/binaries-needed-full.txt lines 470/480).
	  This is the actual ALSA-sequencer client that makes cores' MIDI
	  ports appear at all -- see docs/midi-mt32-parity.md for why
	  package-manifest.md's "driven directly by the MiSTer binary, not
	  a daemon" note (written before this P0.3 binary was traced to its
	  upstream source) undersold this.

	  Sourced from MiSTer-devel/MidiLink_MiSTer (GPL-3.0+), the
	  project's own official repo (an actively-mirrored community fork,
	  bbond007/MiSTer_MidiLink, exists but was not used -- no evidence
	  it diverges in ways relevant here, and the official repo is
	  simpler to justify as the pin). No release tags exist upstream,
	  so this pins an exact commit (see midilink.mk).

	  Rebuilt against THIS system's alsa-lib (BR2_PACKAGE_ALSA_LIB_SEQ)
	  rather than the arm-linux-gnueabihf-prebuilt alsa headers/libs
	  upstream's own Makefile vendors under alsa/ (G4: do not vendor).

	  Runtime companions, both optional and independently toggled:
	    - BR2_PACKAGE_MUNT (mt32d) for the "MUNT" uartmode.
	    - BR2_PACKAGE_FLUIDSYNTH (+_ALSA_LIB, already enabled) for the
	      "FSYNTH" uartmode -- MidiLink shells out to a bare
	      "fluidsynth" and relies on $PATH, so it does not matter that
	      Buildroot's fluidsynth.mk installs to usr/bin while stock's
	      shipped usr/sbin; both are on this image's PATH.
	  Neither is a hard dependency: MidiLink's default uartmode
	  (USBMIDI, a real USB MIDI adapter) needs neither.

	  https://github.com/MiSTer-devel/MidiLink_MiSTer

comment "midilink needs a toolchain w/ threads"
	depends on !BR2_TOOLCHAIN_HAS_THREADS
